Durban - The man accused of kidnapping Sydenham boy, Miguel Louw earlier this year, has been officially arrested for the 9-year-old's murder.
The accused, Mohammed Ebrahim, was due to appear in the Durban Magistrate's Court on Wednesday in connection with Louw's disappearance. 

While seated at the court, Ebrahim was approached by Warrant Officer Rajan Govender and informed of the charge against him.


 






